<Link id="l00033" /><CodeLine lineNumber="33"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Data Dependence Graph Node</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00034" /><CodeLine lineNumber="34"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The graph can represent the following types of nodes:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00035" /><CodeLine lineNumber="35"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 1 Single instruction node containing just one instruction.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00036" /><CodeLine lineNumber="36"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 2 Multiple instruction node where two or more instructions from</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00037" /><CodeLine lineNumber="37"><Highlight kind="comment">///    the same basic block are merged into one node.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="38"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 3 Pi-block node which is a group of other DDG nodes that are part of a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00039" /><CodeLine lineNumber="39"><Highlight kind="comment">///    strongly-connected component of the graph.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00040" /><CodeLine lineNumber="40"><Highlight kind="comment">///    A pi-block node contains more than one single or multiple instruction</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00041" /><CodeLine lineNumber="41"><Highlight kind="comment">///    nodes. The root node cannot be part of a pi-block.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00042" /><CodeLine lineNumber="42"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 4 Root node is a special node that connects to all components such that</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00043" /><CodeLine lineNumber="43"><Highlight kind="comment">///    there is always a path from it to any node in the graph.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00165" /><CodeLine lineNumber="165"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Replacing all the SCCs with pi-blocks results in an acyclic representation</Highlight></CodeLine>
